PLOT PCA DATA IN 3D!

Requirements:

  - r
  - optparse
  - rgl

Usage:

  Rscript -i /path/to/score_data -a /path/to/arrow_data -l
  

-i / --input (required)

A tab-delimited file with the x/y/z coordinates plus (i) unique group id (string), (ii) color (any HTML color code) & (iii) shape (see below) for each datapoint.  

Supported shapes

- "CIRCLE"   ( -> SPHERES.     )
- "SQUARE"   ( -> CUBES        )
- "TRIANGLE" ( -> TETRAHEDRONS )
- "DIAMOND"  ( -> OCTAHEDRONS  )


-a / --arrows (optional)

A tab-delimited file with the x/y/z coordinates for tips of loading arrows plus the relevant variable name (string).


-l / --labels (optional)

Show loading arrow variable names.

-o / --output (optinal)

Specify output name (Default: "output")
